                        "content": "A client is taking ticlopidine hydrochloride. The nurse would tell the client to avoid which substance while taking this medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nTiclopidine hydrochloride is a platelet aggregation inhibitor. It is used to decrease the risk of thrombotic stroke in clients with precursor symptoms. Because it is an antiplatelet agent, other medications that precipitate or aggravate bleeding would be avoided during its use. Therefore, aspirin or any aspirin-containing product needs to be avoided. The substances in options 1, 2, and 3 are safe to consume.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the substance to avoid in the client taking ticlopidine hydrochloride. Recalling that this medication is an antiplatelet agent will direct you to option 4.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Cardiovascular: Antiplatelets\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Neurological: Stroke\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Safety, Patient Education\nStrategies: Subject",
                        "id": "62589259069e41c8b7c9a41766d176a8",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "fe069eb353e2447e9b57677cfd42796e",
                                "content": "\"I'll take my medicine with meals.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a79d0672d0794dd19ef66c998b7f9fea",
                                "content": "\"Blood work will be done every 2 weeks for the first 3 months.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e4bfa5d4fa774c288051087f9e27834c",
                                "content": "\"I would not stop the medication without talking to my doctor first.\""
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "bacaa4b0a5074adf83b296e7d130e8ba",
                                "content": "\"Food will affect the medication, so I need to take the medication on an empty stomach.\""
