                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nTiclopidine is an antiplatelet agent that is used for the prevention of thrombotic stroke. Ticlopidine is best tolerated when taken with meals. Blood work is monitored closely, particularly in early therapy, because the medication can cause neutropenia. A client would not stop medication without the primary health care provider's permission.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, need for further teaching. This phrasing indicates a negative event query and directs you to select an incorrect statement. General principles related to client education regarding medications will assist in eliminating option 3. Regarding the remaining choices, recalling that the complete blood count is monitored and that the medication is taken with food to minimize gastrointestinal upset will direct you to the correct option.\n \n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Evaluate Outcomes\nCognitive Ability: Evaluating\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Cardiovascular: Antiplatelets\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Neurological: Stroke\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Perfusion, Patient Education\nStrategies: Negative Event Query, Strategic Words",
