                        "content": "A client is scheduled to take ticlopidine. The nurse plans to take which action before implementing this medication therapy?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nTiclopidine is an antiplatelet agent that is used for the prevention of thrombotic stroke. Ticlopidine's effects last for the life of the platelet, 7 to 10 days. Ticlopidine also can cause neutropenia, which is an abnormally small number of mature white blood cells (WBCs). Baseline data from a CBC count are necessary before implementation of therapy, and the nurse would monitor for neutropenia during this medication therapy. If this adverse effect does occur, the primary health care provider is notified and therapy needs to be stopped. The effects of neutropenia are reversible within 1 to 3 weeks. Options 1, 2, and 3 are actions that are not specific to this medication therapy.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, nursing actions related to ticlopidine. Recalling that this medication is an antiplatelet agent that affects the WBCs will direct you to the correct option.\n \n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Pharmacology: Cardiovascular: Antiplatelets\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Neurological: Stroke\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Cellular Regulation, Perfusion\nStrategies: Subject",
                        "id": "aa90634ac62642f684d5240a0a8efcb0",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
